# Vercel-specific upload exclusions.
#
# Vercel reads .gitignore at the workspace root only · it does NOT walk into
# nested .gitignore files. Our monorepo has a Rust anchor program at
# programs/purupuru-anchor/ with its own .gitignore that excludes target/
# (8000+ build-artifact files · 100s of MB). Without a top-level rule,
# vercel tries to upload all of them and the chunked-upload aborts.
#
# Same logic for the other nested artifact dirs we don't need at deploy time.

# Rust build artifacts (anchor program · we deploy the .so to Solana, NOT to Vercel)
**/target/

# Loa framework state (state-zone · session memory · not part of the deployed app)
.beads/
.run/
.ck/
grimoires/loa/a2a/
grimoires/loa/analytics/
grimoires/loa/audit-archive/
grimoires/loa/proposals/
grimoires/loa/feedback/
grimoires/loa/memory/

# Eval fixtures (intentional bug fixtures · don't ship to runtime)
evals/

# Local secrets (gitignored · belt-and-suspenders for vercel too)
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Local IDE / OS noise
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/

# Test snapshots + coverage reports
coverage/
**/__snapshots__/
